   moral support evidenced by joint abstention. When the consequences were
   perceived as relatively less severe, consumers found friendship through
   partnering in crime by both indulging. Throughout, guilt underlies the
   relationship between self-control behaviors and social outcomes, as peer
   compliance reduces guilt and thus improves affiliation.
