   an additional, novel downstream consequence of guilt, showing that only
   guilt has the unique motivational consequence of activating a general
   desire to improve the self, which subsequently spills into other domains
   and spurs self-improving product choices. These findings are discussed
   in light of their implications for research on the distinct motivational
