   round numbers. The current research attempts to enrich this literature
   by introducing a new theoretical perspective. Drawing on recent findings
   in the numerical cognition literature, this work proposes that
   individuals project gendered meanings to precise versus round numbers,
   with precise numbers seen as more masculine relative to round ones.
