   respectability (respectability) is one such arrangement. Respectability
   makes life more tolerable by offering a counternarrative that disavows
   stigma through status-oriented displays. This strategy of action emerged
   alongside mass consumer culture in the late 19th century, but what
   relevance does it have to those who are stigmatized in contemporary
   consumer culture? Based on ethnographic interviews and observations with
   middle-class African Americans, respectability remains an important
   strategy that has undergone profound changes since its origins while
   still operating in similar ways. In the late 20th century it fractured
