   provide evidence for the proposed mechanism; and rule out alternative
   accounts, including perceived financial knowledge, expertise and
   self-efficacy perceptions, decision confidence, and preference for
   numerical information. The findings contribute to research on thinking
   styles and decision avoidance, and they underscore a unique
