   research sheds light on an unexpected yet crucial consequence of
   curiosity-that unsatisfied curiosity tempts indulgent consumption in
   domains unrelated to the source of the curiosity. This effect is
   explained by a generalized desire for rewards. Experiments 1-3 establish
   and replicate the proposed mediation model of curiosity -> desire for
   rewards -> indulgence, employing manipulation-of-process,
   moderation-of-process, and measurement-of-process experimental designs.
