   increase goal commitment). However, less is known about how to sustain
   the pursuit of a nonconscious goal, a reality that is reflected in the
   common finding that nonconscious goal pursuit typically persists for
   only one choice episode. This research investigates two factors that
   help sustain the pursuit of a nonconscious goal: increasing the level of
   goal activation prior to goal pursuit and limiting the extent of goal
   deactivation after a goal-consistent behavior. When one of these two
